cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on representing software systems with networks and proposes different applications of community detection to software engineering. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper explores community structure in complex networks, which is a common topic in this sub-category. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper uses class dependency networks to represent software systems, which is related to programming languages. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper analyzes complex software systems, which can be seen as a type of control system. 
- cs.CY (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses network analysis techniques, which can be related to computational geometry.
